WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:00:18.940 --> 00:00:23.880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:29.260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:37.010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

00:00:38.210 --> 00:00:43.120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

00:00:44.650 --> 00:00:47.930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

00:00:47.930 --> 00:00:51.000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

00:00:51.710 --> 00:00:56.660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

00:00:57.700 --> 00:01:00.880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:04.160
♪The open sky rises high♪

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:09.830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:13.860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

00:01:13.860 --> 00:01:17.220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

00:01:17.630 --> 00:01:23.300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

00:01:23.710 --> 00:01:26.960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

00:01:26.960 --> 00:01:30.290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:34.730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

00:01:34.730 --> 00:01:35.980
=The Lead=

00:01:36.060 --> 00:01:37.940
=Episode 7=

00:01:40.550 --> 00:01:42.510
Lunch time! Lunch time!

00:01:44.560 --> 00:01:45.750
I want to be the first.

00:01:46.320 --> 00:01:47.640
No, I'm the first.

00:01:48.270 --> 00:01:50.050
♪The hostile forces are brought down♪

00:01:50.590 --> 00:01:52.550
Kids from the trainee class, listen up.

00:01:52.920 --> 00:01:55.030
Take your food back to the dorms.

00:01:55.390 --> 00:01:56.800
The cafeteria is packed.

00:01:57.440 --> 00:01:59.390
Okay.

00:02:01.560 --> 00:02:03.400
♪A wave of socialist building♪

00:02:05.600 --> 00:02:07.030
No meat again?

00:02:07.030 --> 00:02:10.180
♪The Party leads the people well♪

00:02:10.200 --> 00:02:11.040
Here.

00:02:12.430 --> 00:02:13.280
- Here.
- Thanks.

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:14.320
Come on, hurry.

00:02:14.520 --> 00:02:15.640
Next.

00:02:16.730 --> 00:02:19.330
♪Firmly follow the Communist Party♪

00:02:21.150 --> 00:02:22.640
Next.

00:02:24.710 --> 00:02:25.550
Is it not enough?

00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:26.960
Hurry up. We need to eat too.

00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:28.350
We don't have enough to eat.

00:02:28.880 --> 00:02:30.640
We still need to eat.

00:02:31.790 --> 00:02:33.560
Why take my white Mo?

00:02:33.560 --> 00:02:35.880
Come on, I gave you two black ones.

00:02:35.880 --> 00:02:36.750
Go, go.

00:02:37.030 --> 00:02:37.870
Hurry up.

00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:39.320
Finally, it's my turn.

00:02:39.320 --> 00:02:43.190
♪The socialist society will triumph♪

00:02:44.280 --> 00:02:45.120
Is that enough?

00:02:46.940 --> 00:02:48.680
♪Will surely come♪

00:02:48.953 --> 00:02:49.840
Why only two black Mo?

00:02:49.840 --> 00:02:50.760
Hurry up for the food!

00:02:50.760 --> 00:02:51.680
Wait for me.

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:54.070
They picked on you?

00:02:57.120 --> 00:02:58.040
All right, go.

00:02:59.070 --> 00:03:00.230
Hey, Qiu.

00:03:01.710 --> 00:03:03.070
Why pick on the kid?

00:03:03.280 --> 00:03:04.120
What's wrong?

00:03:04.280 --> 00:03:05.120
What happened?

00:03:05.400 --> 00:03:07.120
Why did my kid get two black Mo?

00:03:07.510 --> 00:03:09.710
Everyone else gets
one black and one white.

00:03:10.350 --> 00:03:11.510
It isn't enough for your kid,

00:03:11.510 --> 00:03:13.680
so I traded one white
for two black ones.

00:03:13.680 --> 00:03:14.713
How's that picking on her?

00:03:19.640 --> 00:03:21.510
There are only two black Mo here.

00:03:21.510 --> 00:03:22.360
Where's the white one?

00:03:22.360 --> 00:03:23.310
I ate one.

00:03:26.716 --> 00:03:28.383
Look at how little food
you gave the kid.

00:03:28.394 --> 00:03:29.639
How could she get full on that?

00:03:29.650 --> 00:03:31.510
Everyone gets the same dishes. Look.

00:03:31.680 --> 00:03:33.070
The kitchen staff are heartless.

00:03:33.430 --> 00:03:34.836
You even skimp on the kids' rations.

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:36.640
They're growing and practicing.

00:03:39.310 --> 00:03:41.840
Each trainee gets
21 jin of grain a month.

00:03:42.510 --> 00:03:43.870
That averages 7 liang a day.

00:03:43.870 --> 00:03:45.630
Three Mo are already 6 liang.

00:03:45.870 --> 00:03:48.750
Your kid finished a month's rations
in ten days.

00:03:49.590 --> 00:03:50.710
Is she a trainee?

00:03:51.190 --> 00:03:52.280
She's a hungry wolf.

00:03:53.680 --> 00:03:55.400
Hey, Qiu, watch your mouth.

00:03:56.560 --> 00:03:58.750
These are successors to communism.

00:03:59.710 --> 00:04:01.560
And you call them hungry wolves?

00:04:03.800 --> 00:04:04.720
Don't bully an old man.

00:04:04.960 --> 00:04:05.800
Come at me instead.

00:04:05.960 --> 00:04:07.590
Yeah, I'm talking to Qiu.

00:04:07.590 --> 00:04:08.630
None of your business.

00:04:08.630 --> 00:04:09.730
Serving food is my business.

00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:11.310
Fine, fine. I won't push it.

00:04:11.310 --> 00:04:12.150
We're leaving.

00:04:12.150 --> 00:04:13.840
You're not going anywhere.

00:04:16.340 --> 00:04:17.190
What are you doing?

00:04:17.190 --> 00:04:18.120
Apologize to Master Qiu.

00:04:18.120 --> 00:04:20.120
Loose tongue. I'm not afraid of you.

00:04:20.870 --> 00:04:21.710
Fine.

00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:23.080
What do you want?

00:04:23.240 --> 00:04:24.080
Mr. Hu,

00:04:25.840 --> 00:04:26.910
with just one drumstick,

00:04:26.910 --> 00:04:28.280
can you play a whole show?

00:04:30.150 --> 00:04:31.590
The whole kitchen crew is joining in.

00:04:32.430 --> 00:04:33.680
Qiu really has it rough.

00:04:34.150 --> 00:04:35.590
With this tiny food budget,

00:04:35.870 --> 00:04:37.310
we have to last the month.

00:04:37.310 --> 00:04:38.560
The old man wishes every cent

00:04:38.560 --> 00:04:40.120
could be stretched eight ways.

00:04:40.610 --> 00:04:42.020
Just to keep your kid fed

00:04:42.031 --> 00:04:43.151
and still stick to the rules,

00:04:43.162 --> 00:04:45.555
what's wrong with trading one white Mo
for two black ones?

00:04:45.960 --> 00:04:47.560
And you don't appreciate it?

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:49.430
You joke about Qiu all the time.

00:04:49.430 --> 00:04:51.360
I'm fine with that, but you can't make

00:04:51.630 --> 00:04:52.470
a big deal of this.

00:04:52.840 --> 00:04:53.680
Apologize.

00:04:54.310 --> 00:04:55.520
What am I even doing this for?

00:04:56.150 --> 00:04:57.710
I'm done with the kitchen.

00:04:58.190 --> 00:04:59.430
Whoever wants it can run it.

00:05:01.910 --> 00:05:02.910
Why look at me?

00:05:03.360 --> 00:05:04.840
You upset him; you fix it.

00:05:13.150 --> 00:05:14.156
Come on, serve me food.

00:05:14.167 --> 00:05:15.190
I still have to practice.

00:05:15.190 --> 00:05:16.143
No one's getting served.

00:05:16.430 --> 00:05:17.360
I call the shots.

00:05:18.970 --> 00:05:19.840
Right, right.

00:05:19.840 --> 00:05:20.680
Right, that's right.

00:05:20.870 --> 00:05:22.120
Fine, Qiu, I was wrong.

00:05:22.120 --> 00:05:23.080
I apologize.

00:05:23.310 --> 00:05:24.190
You're right.

00:05:24.190 --> 00:05:25.030
No.

00:05:27.240 --> 00:05:28.240
What more do you want?

00:05:28.630 --> 00:05:29.630
I already apologized.

00:05:32.400 --> 00:05:34.120
I was wrong and said sorry. What else?

00:05:34.120 --> 00:05:34.960
Still no.

00:05:39.280 --> 00:05:40.310
You geezer.

00:05:40.590 --> 00:05:42.120
I've got half a Xifeng Liquor left.

00:05:42.120 --> 00:05:42.960
Do you want it?

00:05:43.080 --> 00:05:44.206
Bring it to my room tonight.

00:05:51.430 --> 00:05:53.870
This time, I went with the leaders

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:55.800
from the County Revolutionary Committee

00:05:55.800 --> 00:05:57.190
to several nearby sister counties.

00:05:57.800 --> 00:05:59.120
Only then did I see

00:05:59.510 --> 00:06:02.040
their County Troupes stage model operas.

00:06:03.510 --> 00:06:04.560
Now, look at us.

00:06:06.240 --> 00:06:07.720
A whole year has gone by,

00:06:07.920 --> 00:06:10.040
and we've only done opera excerpts.

00:06:10.310 --> 00:06:12.120
It's embarrassing, comrades.

00:06:12.430 --> 00:06:14.920
At the meeting,
the leaders harshly criticized

00:06:14.920 --> 00:06:16.510
our troupe repeatedly.

00:06:16.870 --> 00:06:19.800
They want a full-length play soon

00:06:20.160 --> 00:06:21.040
for the rural tour.

00:06:26.870 --> 00:06:28.560
What are you even writing down?

00:06:28.560 --> 00:06:29.920
What did I say that's worth noting?

00:06:30.160 --> 00:06:31.070
The spirit of it.

00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:33.160
It's all about the spirit.

00:06:33.160 --> 00:06:35.360
Enough spirit. I'm losing my mind.

00:06:36.870 --> 00:06:37.830
Deputy Director Zhu,

00:06:38.160 --> 00:06:39.680
you're in charge of creation.

00:06:39.950 --> 00:06:41.120
Give us your stance.

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:47.160
Our biggest problem now

00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:49.190
is that we're short on actors.

00:06:49.750 --> 00:06:51.070
There's no one to take over.

00:06:52.800 --> 00:06:54.190
For the Eight Model Operas,

00:06:54.190 --> 00:06:56.190
what we can pull together now

00:06:56.190 --> 00:06:57.720
is probably Hong Deng Ji.

00:06:58.360 --> 00:07:00.750
And our past shows of Hong Deng Ji

00:07:01.270 --> 00:07:02.510
were really well received.

00:07:02.510 --> 00:07:04.120
They were a big success, right?

00:07:05.190 --> 00:07:06.030
Director,

00:07:08.040 --> 00:07:08.920
can you direct it?

00:07:09.630 --> 00:07:11.830
Troupe Leader, I can. No problem.

00:07:12.870 --> 00:07:14.870
But we have one major problem now.

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:17.360
Ms. Cui, who plays Grandma Li,

00:07:17.360 --> 00:07:19.240
has lost her voice. She can't sing.

00:07:19.830 --> 00:07:21.310
So, who will play Grandma Li?

00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:31.120
I have a rough idea.

00:07:31.120 --> 00:07:34.120
Let Hua Caixiang and Mi Lan

00:07:34.510 --> 00:07:35.600
play Grandma Li

00:07:35.950 --> 00:07:37.160
and Li Tiemei, respectively.

00:07:37.160 --> 00:07:38.000
How's that?

00:07:38.830 --> 00:07:41.630
Who's the grandma? Who's the kid?

00:07:41.870 --> 00:07:43.190
Who's the director here?

00:07:43.190 --> 00:07:44.800
What do you mean by that?

00:07:45.630 --> 00:07:47.310
You're in creative work.

00:07:47.310 --> 00:07:48.510
You can't dump this conflict

00:07:48.510 --> 00:07:49.430
on me.

00:07:49.430 --> 00:07:50.310
Shall we switch jobs?

00:07:51.600 --> 00:07:53.190
Rank really crushes people, huh?

00:07:53.190 --> 00:07:54.920
Who are you saying that to?

00:07:54.920 --> 00:07:56.070
Director Huang is right here.

00:07:56.430 --> 00:07:57.533
He's one rank above me.

00:07:57.544 --> 00:07:58.600
Are you talking about him?

00:07:58.600 --> 00:08:00.390
What ranks are you on about?

00:08:00.750 --> 00:08:02.630
Don't bring that mindset
into the troupe.

00:08:02.920 --> 00:08:03.920
That's settled, then.

00:08:04.630 --> 00:08:05.470
Meeting adjourned.

00:08:09.510 --> 00:08:10.750
Settled? What was settled?

00:08:11.360 --> 00:08:12.360
Hong Deng Ji.

00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:14.040
Hurry up.

00:08:14.040 --> 00:08:15.160
Coming, coming.

00:08:16.360 --> 00:08:18.510
We're going home. Why braid your hair?

00:08:18.510 --> 00:08:20.270
Let's go to the park this weekend.

00:08:21.070 --> 00:08:22.040
Come to my place.

00:08:22.040 --> 00:08:23.190
My mom will make goodies.

00:08:23.190 --> 00:08:24.190
Like what?

00:08:24.830 --> 00:08:25.883
You'll know when you come.

00:08:26.240 --> 00:08:27.630
Xiuying, hurry up.

00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:31.510
I'm coming. Let's go.

00:08:31.510 --> 00:08:32.610
- Come on.
- Let's go.

00:08:59.800 --> 00:09:01.166
You'll be alone in the dorm again.

00:09:03.600 --> 00:09:04.440
Same here.

00:09:08.750 --> 00:09:09.590
Hu Sanyuan.

00:09:10.270 --> 00:09:11.110
Where are you headed?

00:09:11.510 --> 00:09:12.680
To the trainee's dorm

00:09:13.070 --> 00:09:14.000
for my niece.

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:15.950
Come on. I need you. Hurry.

00:09:16.750 --> 00:09:17.600
What's going on?

00:09:17.600 --> 00:09:18.510
Let's talk over drinks.

00:09:20.830 --> 00:09:25.430
Tiemei is something else.

00:09:25.720 --> 00:09:29.600
Years? What? Only 17?

00:09:30.310 --> 00:09:31.800
I guess it's about years.

00:09:32.510 --> 00:09:36.040
I guess it's age.

00:09:36.430 --> 00:09:37.310
Age.

00:09:38.720 --> 00:09:39.606
Rock, Paper, Scissors.

00:09:40.630 --> 00:09:42.190
Rock, Paper, Scissors.

00:09:42.830 --> 00:09:44.190
Okay. Age it is.

00:09:44.950 --> 00:09:49.070
Only 17 years old.

00:09:49.920 --> 00:09:56.390
She joined the cause since childhood.

00:09:57.600 --> 00:10:02.040
Bravely fought what enemy?

00:10:02.040 --> 00:10:03.270
How do you read this word?

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:05.430
I don't think it reads "what".

00:10:05.430 --> 00:10:06.750
You goof.

00:10:06.750 --> 00:10:08.510
I mean, what is this word?

00:10:09.240 --> 00:10:10.840
Skip what you don't know. Keep reading.

00:10:11.670 --> 00:10:13.080
Hua Caixiang and Mi Lan

00:10:13.690 --> 00:10:14.550
can both act, right?

00:10:14.550 --> 00:10:15.840
One grandma, one granddaughter.

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:17.840
Will that work?

00:10:17.840 --> 00:10:18.790
Why wouldn't it?

00:10:21.200 --> 00:10:24.120
So, who plays the grandma?
Who's the kid?

00:10:25.510 --> 00:10:26.510
What do you think?

00:10:27.510 --> 00:10:28.630
Mi Lan, maybe.

00:10:28.630 --> 00:10:29.470
She's younger.

00:10:29.910 --> 00:10:30.910
Her voice is too limited.

00:10:31.870 --> 00:10:33.630
Can she really play the grandma?

00:10:35.270 --> 00:10:36.510
Well, if you put it that way,

00:10:36.870 --> 00:10:38.270
neither of them is right for it.

00:10:38.270 --> 00:10:39.670
Hua Caixiang is more versatile.

00:10:40.600 --> 00:10:42.510
She can play grandma and granddaughter.

00:10:43.200 --> 00:10:45.510
If Hua Caixiang plays Tiemei,

00:10:45.510 --> 00:10:47.600
she could go on without rehearsal.

00:10:47.600 --> 00:10:49.270
Mi Lan was an understudy. Same deal.

00:10:49.790 --> 00:10:50.630
Right?

00:10:52.910 --> 00:10:54.320
Don't set me up.

00:10:55.440 --> 00:10:56.870
Have Huang Zhengjing and Zhu Jiru

00:10:56.870 --> 00:10:58.150
go talk to Hua Caixiang.

00:10:59.030 --> 00:11:00.030
They won't go.

00:11:00.630 --> 00:11:01.790
You go yourself.

00:11:04.750 --> 00:11:06.510
When will you repay that favor?

00:11:08.087 --> 00:11:09.500
- I still owe you.
- No, you don't.

00:11:12.120 --> 00:11:14.030
You cultured folks.

00:11:14.030 --> 00:11:15.390
You can't owe cultured folks.

00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:17.390
Take it seriously.

00:11:18.000 --> 00:11:18.840
I'm off.

00:11:29.440 --> 00:11:30.960
Why are you knitting here again?

00:11:31.790 --> 00:11:33.240
In this heat?

00:11:33.240 --> 00:11:34.790
With all that yarn in your lap,

00:11:34.790 --> 00:11:35.810
you're torturing yourself.

00:11:37.360 --> 00:11:38.200
Smell this.

00:11:38.200 --> 00:11:39.060
Take it away.

00:11:39.060 --> 00:11:40.510
Pig's trotters. They smell amazing.

00:11:42.720 --> 00:11:43.560
I'll leave them here.

00:11:48.750 --> 00:11:49.590
Who's that for?

00:11:50.200 --> 00:11:51.080
Mr. Wang.

00:11:51.910 --> 00:11:52.750
Which Mr. Wang?

00:11:53.200 --> 00:11:54.440
Mr. Wang, the jerk.

00:11:57.080 --> 00:11:58.320
You just made me one last year.

00:11:58.320 --> 00:11:59.270
It hasn't worn out yet.

00:11:59.270 --> 00:12:00.150
Why make another one?

00:12:01.120 --> 00:12:02.390
New patterns this year.

00:12:06.630 --> 00:12:08.320
I've got bad news.

00:12:09.790 --> 00:12:12.200
Our lousy troupe may shut down.

00:12:14.240 --> 00:12:15.080
Why?

00:12:17.720 --> 00:12:20.030
Director Glasses just told me:

00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:23.870
County authorities want Hong Deng Ji

00:12:23.870 --> 00:12:24.840
for a rural tour.

00:12:25.870 --> 00:12:27.360
Troupe leaders told them

00:12:27.360 --> 00:12:28.750
we couldn't without actresses.

00:12:30.080 --> 00:12:31.550
County officials got mad and said

00:12:32.200 --> 00:12:34.870
that without plays, the troupe

00:12:34.870 --> 00:12:35.910
should shut down.

00:12:38.320 --> 00:12:39.510
Which actress are we short on?

00:12:39.510 --> 00:12:40.550
Grandma Li.

00:12:44.510 --> 00:12:45.510
So, what to do?

00:12:45.790 --> 00:12:46.670
The way I see it,

00:12:46.910 --> 00:12:49.390
a lousy troupe can't fill a show.

00:12:50.240 --> 00:12:51.510
If it folds, it folds.

00:12:57.030 --> 00:12:57.870
How about this?

00:12:58.240 --> 00:12:59.270
I'll play Grandma Li.

00:12:59.670 --> 00:13:00.750
Have Mi Lan

00:13:00.750 --> 00:13:01.600
play Tiemei.

00:13:10.120 --> 00:13:11.550
Go tell Director Glasses my answer.

00:13:13.200 --> 00:13:14.040
What answer?

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:17.360
You want to play the part,

00:13:17.720 --> 00:13:19.120
so you should tell him.

00:13:23.270 --> 00:13:24.120
Well...

00:13:24.240 --> 00:13:25.080
Get lost.

00:13:30.510 --> 00:13:31.350
Uh...

00:13:32.200 --> 00:13:33.360
Mi Lan, washing up?

00:13:33.670 --> 00:13:34.510
Bro.

00:13:38.510 --> 00:13:40.510
How did your soap get so tiny?

00:13:41.240 --> 00:13:42.320
Here, here, use mine.

00:13:43.120 --> 00:13:44.390
Director Glasses brought it back

00:13:44.390 --> 00:13:45.600
from Shanghai that year.

00:13:45.600 --> 00:13:46.550
It smells nice. Try it.

00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:48.440
Bro, that doesn't feel right.

00:13:48.853 --> 00:13:50.150
What's wrong? I'll use this one.

00:13:50.150 --> 00:13:50.990
It's fine, really.

00:13:51.240 --> 00:13:52.080
Thanks.

00:13:59.440 --> 00:14:01.080
Our troupe may be disbanded.

00:14:05.200 --> 00:14:06.600
Director Glasses told me

00:14:08.550 --> 00:14:11.720
the county authorities
picked Hong Deng Ji

00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:12.790
for a rural tour.

00:14:14.120 --> 00:14:15.550
Our troupe leaders said

00:14:16.030 --> 00:14:17.630
we couldn't without actresses.

00:14:18.240 --> 00:14:19.630
The county officials heard that

00:14:19.630 --> 00:14:20.600
and got mad right away.

00:14:20.790 --> 00:14:23.150
They said that without plays, the troupe

00:14:23.150 --> 00:14:24.120
should shut down.

00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:33.080
Why not ask which actress we're missing?

00:14:35.510 --> 00:14:36.870
We're missing Grandma Li.

00:14:38.030 --> 00:14:39.440
I've played Hong Deng Ji

00:14:39.440 --> 00:14:40.870
so many times.

00:14:41.390 --> 00:14:42.510
If you ask me,

00:14:43.320 --> 00:14:45.720
Grandma Li is the best-written part.

00:14:46.630 --> 00:14:47.750
To play that role,

00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:50.080
you need real skill to pull it off.

00:14:50.550 --> 00:14:52.120
Not just the singing. I even remember

00:14:52.120 --> 00:14:53.030
the spoken lines.

00:14:56.510 --> 00:14:58.840
It was on a night like that,

00:14:59.240 --> 00:15:01.390
just as dark,

00:15:01.840 --> 00:15:03.440
just as cold.

00:15:04.720 --> 00:15:07.000
I was worried about your grandpa.

00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:08.750
I couldn't sit still.

00:15:08.750 --> 00:15:10.240
I couldn't sleep either.

00:15:10.600 --> 00:15:13.390
I mended clothes under the lamp.

00:15:14.550 --> 00:15:16.840
Soon, someone knocked.

00:15:17.750 --> 00:15:21.270
He shouted, "Ma'am, open up! Hurry!"

00:15:22.080 --> 00:15:23.960
I rushed over and opened the door.

00:15:25.960 --> 00:15:27.720
A man stumbled in.

00:15:28.360 --> 00:15:30.030
That man was your father.

00:15:30.390 --> 00:15:32.440
The father you have now.

00:15:34.390 --> 00:15:37.440
He was covered in wounds.

00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:40.000
In his left hand was a signal lantern.

00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:42.360
In his right arm, he held a child.

00:15:42.360 --> 00:15:44.120
He said,

00:15:44.870 --> 00:15:47.360
"Ma'am, from now on,"

00:15:47.360 --> 00:15:49.510
"I'm your son."

00:15:49.510 --> 00:15:51.510
"And she is your granddaughter."

00:16:03.510 --> 00:16:04.350
Well?

00:16:08.630 --> 00:16:10.750
Why stand right in front of my finger?

00:16:17.670 --> 00:16:18.510
Laidi.

00:16:19.550 --> 00:16:20.390
Are you asleep yet?

00:16:20.960 --> 00:16:21.800
Not yet.

00:16:22.550 --> 00:16:23.510
Are you scared?

00:16:24.030 --> 00:16:25.510
What's there to be scared of?

00:16:26.510 --> 00:16:27.510
I am.

00:16:28.270 --> 00:16:29.440
Let's talk for a bit.

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:30.910
Sure.

00:16:33.120 --> 00:16:34.120
Do you miss home?

00:16:35.000 --> 00:16:36.200
Of course.

00:16:37.320 --> 00:16:38.750
Tell me about your home.

00:16:42.120 --> 00:16:44.080
My family kept three sheep.

00:16:44.080 --> 00:16:46.390
One ewe and two lambs.

00:16:46.840 --> 00:16:48.120
They were very close to me.

00:16:49.790 --> 00:16:51.390
I've never kept sheep.

00:16:52.750 --> 00:16:54.390
But Wang Heiwa from my village and I

00:16:54.390 --> 00:16:55.510
raised a dog together.

00:16:55.870 --> 00:16:56.910
We called him Heiwa too.

00:16:57.080 --> 00:16:58.510
Why are there so many Heiwas?

00:16:59.120 --> 00:16:59.960
Just listen.

00:17:00.360 --> 00:17:02.200
Dog Heiwa slept with me one night,

00:17:02.390 --> 00:17:03.630
and with Wang Heiwa the next.

00:17:04.120 --> 00:17:05.550
I'm telling you. It's really fierce.

00:17:05.550 --> 00:17:07.000
It bites anyone

00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:08.120
who dares to pick on us.

00:17:10.240 --> 00:17:12.360
Have you ever fought Wang Heiwa?

00:17:12.360 --> 00:17:13.240
Yeah.

00:17:14.080 --> 00:17:15.360
Who does Dog Heiwa help?

00:17:16.030 --> 00:17:17.510
Now, that's the right question.

00:17:18.840 --> 00:17:19.750
Let me show you.

00:17:20.270 --> 00:17:21.240
When we start fighting,

00:17:21.390 --> 00:17:24.440
it goes, whoof, whoof.

00:17:24.670 --> 00:17:25.510
It stands between us.

00:17:25.510 --> 00:17:27.200
Whoof, whoof, whoof.

00:17:27.200 --> 00:17:29.200
Howling nonstop like that.

00:17:29.720 --> 00:17:31.270
Poor Dog Heiwa gets so torn up.

00:17:51.240 --> 00:17:52.630
I miss Dog Heiwa.

00:17:58.200 --> 00:17:59.630
I miss my sheep too.

00:18:02.720 --> 00:18:04.080
I don't want to learn opera.

00:18:05.200 --> 00:18:06.150
I want to go home.

00:18:07.200 --> 00:18:08.040
What about you?

00:18:10.910 --> 00:18:12.000
Why did you stop talking?

00:18:13.870 --> 00:18:15.000
Does your leg hurt?

00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:16.630
Yeah.

00:18:17.200 --> 00:18:18.120
It hurts like crazy.

00:18:53.510 --> 00:18:54.350
Line up!

00:18:56.240 --> 00:18:57.350
We're missing three.

00:18:58.160 --> 00:18:59.960
Feng Xiaoxiao, which boys are missing?

00:19:00.510 --> 00:19:01.440
Sir,

00:19:01.440 --> 00:19:03.510
Li Chunsheng and Liu Ke
went home on Saturday.

00:19:03.510 --> 00:19:04.440
They haven't come back.

00:19:04.790 --> 00:19:05.909
Jiahe, what about the girls?

00:19:06.070 --> 00:19:07.000
Mr. He,

00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:08.160
Yu Liping isn't here either.

00:19:08.160 --> 00:19:10.030
Her mom said she can't walk.

00:19:10.350 --> 00:19:11.750
From now on, if any of you

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:13.070
don't want to learn,

00:19:13.070 --> 00:19:14.790
train hard, or take the pain,

00:19:14.790 --> 00:19:16.030
come and tell me.

00:19:16.030 --> 00:19:17.880
Plenty of people want in this troupe.

00:19:17.880 --> 00:19:19.160
Don't hold a spot you won't use.

00:19:19.380 --> 00:19:20.240
Do you hear me?

00:19:20.250 --> 00:19:21.550
Yes.

00:19:21.730 --> 00:19:22.640
Isn't that Liu Ke?

00:19:22.640 --> 00:19:23.590
Go practice.

00:19:23.590 --> 00:19:24.680
I don't want to.

00:19:25.200 --> 00:19:27.310
I'm done with opera. I quit.

00:19:28.920 --> 00:19:30.270
Even if you beat me, I won't go.

00:19:30.270 --> 00:19:32.160
Are you going or not? Are you?

00:19:32.960 --> 00:19:34.680
Are you going or not?

00:19:38.200 --> 00:19:39.040
What's going on?

00:19:40.160 --> 00:19:41.110
Mr. He,

00:19:41.110 --> 00:19:42.400
this little brat

00:19:42.400 --> 00:19:43.590
says practice is too hard

00:19:43.590 --> 00:19:44.460
and wants to quit.

00:19:44.470 --> 00:19:46.070
It's only been days, and he'll quit?

00:19:46.070 --> 00:19:47.030
Mr. He, I...

00:19:47.510 --> 00:19:48.510
- You brat.
- Liu Ke.

00:19:48.510 --> 00:19:49.680
- You lied to me!
- Liu Ke.

00:19:49.680 --> 00:19:51.090
Run. Just wait till I catch you.

00:19:51.100 --> 00:19:51.950
I'll break your legs.

00:19:51.960 --> 00:19:53.110
Go. Bring Liu Ke back.

00:19:53.110 --> 00:19:53.950
Yes, sir.

00:19:55.440 --> 00:19:56.510
Liu Ke, stop right there!

00:19:56.510 --> 00:19:57.350
Stop!

00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:00.720
We don't need this many. Hey.

00:20:02.880 --> 00:20:03.720
Don't move.

00:20:04.680 --> 00:20:05.640
Stop right there.

00:20:05.640 --> 00:20:07.110
We're a team.

00:20:07.110 --> 00:20:08.350
- Mr. He.
- Get back here!

00:20:08.350 --> 00:20:09.190
I'll go after him.

00:20:11.920 --> 00:20:13.440
Liu Ke, stop right there!

00:20:13.790 --> 00:20:15.160
- I'll catch you!
- Stop!

00:20:15.160 --> 00:20:16.446
- I'll break your legs!
- Stop!

00:20:16.510 --> 00:20:18.070
I'll break your legs!

00:20:18.510 --> 00:20:19.510
Help!

00:20:19.790 --> 00:20:21.350
Liu Ke, stop right there!

00:20:21.350 --> 00:20:22.350
Stop!

00:20:22.350 --> 00:20:23.550
Do we need this many people?

00:20:23.880 --> 00:20:25.550
You little brat, stop running!

00:20:25.550 --> 00:20:26.880
Are you out of your mind?

00:20:26.880 --> 00:20:28.270
Stop chasing me!

00:20:28.880 --> 00:20:29.790
Stop, Liu Ke.

00:20:29.790 --> 00:20:30.630
Stop!

00:20:34.110 --> 00:20:35.400
Don't come any closer!

00:20:35.830 --> 00:20:36.880
I'll fight you all!

00:20:37.200 --> 00:20:38.040
Stay back!

00:20:38.400 --> 00:20:40.590
Fool, aren't you a fast runner?

00:20:40.590 --> 00:20:41.510
Keep running, then.

00:20:41.830 --> 00:20:42.750
Run out of town.

00:20:43.720 --> 00:20:45.270
Do you want to practice?

00:20:45.270 --> 00:20:46.750
Fool, run!

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:47.960
Liu Ke, run!

00:20:47.960 --> 00:20:49.350
- After him!
- Liu Ke, run!

00:20:49.640 --> 00:20:50.480
Run!

00:20:59.510 --> 00:21:01.000
What's going on?

00:21:01.000 --> 00:21:02.680
Like tossing buns to a dog.

00:21:02.960 --> 00:21:04.030
They're not coming back.

00:21:04.030 --> 00:21:04.880
Mr. He,

00:21:05.510 --> 00:21:06.680
let's go look for them.

00:21:06.960 --> 00:21:08.270
Sure, sure.

00:21:08.270 --> 00:21:09.110
Sure, my foot.

00:21:09.550 --> 00:21:10.510
Don't make this harder.

00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:13.110
Chu Jiahe, lead them back to the troupe.

00:21:13.110 --> 00:21:14.136
Don't leave anyone behind.

00:21:14.640 --> 00:21:15.480
Hurry.

00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:16.840
Come with me.

00:21:21.510 --> 00:21:22.440
I want to go too.

00:21:34.590 --> 00:21:36.510
Heiwa, I'm begging you.

00:21:36.510 --> 00:21:37.350
Let me go.

00:21:37.350 --> 00:21:38.830
- I can't.
- Let me go.

00:21:38.830 --> 00:21:40.160
I swear I won't run.

00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:41.000
I don't believe you.

00:21:41.010 --> 00:21:42.070
I'll give you five cents.

00:21:42.070 --> 00:21:42.910
I don't want it.

00:21:43.070 --> 00:21:44.400
You little flatterer.

00:21:44.400 --> 00:21:45.880
All you do is flatter Feng Xiaoxiao.

00:21:45.880 --> 00:21:46.720
I want to.

00:21:47.790 --> 00:21:48.960
Feng Xiaoxiao,

00:21:49.160 --> 00:21:50.480
have someone else watch me.

00:22:00.880 --> 00:22:02.880
Are you ready?

00:22:02.880 --> 00:22:05.000
Always ready.

00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:09.350
We are all members
of the Communist Children's League.

00:22:09.350 --> 00:22:12.350
The future will surely be ours.

00:22:12.350 --> 00:22:13.403
Don't stick your butt out.

00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:14.840
Head up.

00:22:19.960 --> 00:22:20.880
That's weird.

00:22:21.830 --> 00:22:23.200
Why doesn't stretching hurt today?

00:22:23.680 --> 00:22:25.160
Yeah, it feels way easier.

00:22:25.160 --> 00:22:26.669
Right? Did I get better,

00:22:26.680 --> 00:22:27.790
or did the barre get lower?

00:22:27.790 --> 00:22:28.660
- Zhou Yuzhi.
- We...

00:22:28.670 --> 00:22:29.756
What are you talking about?

00:22:30.200 --> 00:22:32.070
You always have so much to say.

00:22:32.792 --> 00:22:34.018
Hold your feet with both hands.

00:22:37.510 --> 00:22:38.590
Push down harder.

00:22:53.720 --> 00:22:54.713
Who told you to get down?

00:22:54.960 --> 00:22:55.800
Get back up.

00:23:02.510 --> 00:23:03.350
Who did this?

00:23:06.920 --> 00:23:07.760
Who did this?

00:23:11.880 --> 00:23:13.790
I'm giving you one last chance.

00:23:15.960 --> 00:23:16.800
Liu Ke.

00:23:17.510 --> 00:23:18.400
Who did it?

00:23:18.400 --> 00:23:19.880
Sir, it really wasn't me.

00:23:19.880 --> 00:23:20.720
Then who was it?

00:23:21.000 --> 00:23:22.470
- Who did it?
- I don't know.

00:23:22.590 --> 00:23:23.910
- Who did it?
- I don't know.

00:23:24.030 --> 00:23:24.920
Who did it?

00:23:24.920 --> 00:23:25.960
Sir, it wasn't me.

00:23:25.960 --> 00:23:27.146
Then who was it? Who did it?

00:23:27.157 --> 00:23:28.310
- I don't know.
- Who did it?

00:23:28.310 --> 00:23:29.200
It wasn't me.

00:23:29.200 --> 00:23:30.680
No lunch until someone talks.

00:23:30.980 --> 00:23:31.830
Who did it?

00:23:31.830 --> 00:23:32.830
It wasn't me.

00:23:32.830 --> 00:23:33.720
Who did it?

00:23:35.440 --> 00:23:36.910
- Still won't talk?
- It wasn't me.

00:23:37.070 --> 00:23:37.910
Talk.

00:23:38.463 --> 00:23:39.350
Are you going to talk?

00:23:46.030 --> 00:23:47.030
Still not talking, huh?

00:23:47.310 --> 00:23:48.680
You're all so stubborn.

00:23:49.642 --> 00:23:50.828
No lunch until someone talks.

00:23:51.030 --> 00:23:51.870
Stand properly.

00:23:52.720 --> 00:23:53.560
Mr. He,

00:23:54.070 --> 00:23:55.310
it wasn't us girls.

00:23:55.310 --> 00:23:56.550
Why can't we eat?

00:23:56.550 --> 00:23:57.400
Exactly.

00:23:57.440 --> 00:23:58.920
Girls dismissed. Go eat.

00:23:59.590 --> 00:24:00.590
That's not fair to us.

00:24:01.270 --> 00:24:03.070
Quiet. Boys, stand straight.

00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:06.720
Step forward.

00:24:07.510 --> 00:24:08.440
Stop talking.

00:24:10.790 --> 00:24:12.510
Talk, or no dinner.

00:24:14.000 --> 00:24:15.000
Keep your eyes open.

00:24:15.880 --> 00:24:16.720
Look at these dishes.

00:24:17.240 --> 00:24:18.310
See what you want to eat.

00:24:19.510 --> 00:24:20.790
You think I can't handle you?

00:24:25.270 --> 00:24:27.160
Liu Ke, what are you doing?

00:24:28.200 --> 00:24:29.510
Keep your eyes open.

00:24:29.920 --> 00:24:30.920
Watch them eat.

00:24:32.510 --> 00:24:33.880
Still not hungry, huh?

00:24:34.550 --> 00:24:35.550
Which dish do you like?

00:24:35.550 --> 00:24:36.390
All of you, watch.

00:24:37.350 --> 00:24:38.830
Yes, keep your eyes open.

00:24:40.720 --> 00:24:42.830
Look. See which dish smells best.

00:24:45.270 --> 00:24:46.110
What are you doing?

00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:48.840
I did it.

00:24:49.880 --> 00:24:51.070
Her.

00:24:51.270 --> 00:24:52.160
It was her.

00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:53.840
Who were you with?

00:24:54.640 --> 00:24:55.750
I did it by myself.

00:24:55.750 --> 00:24:56.590
No way.

00:24:57.510 --> 00:24:58.960
You couldn't pull that off alone.

00:24:59.920 --> 00:25:00.760
Still not talking?

00:25:01.030 --> 00:25:02.000
Put your bowls down.

00:25:02.593 --> 00:25:03.853
No one eats until someone talks.

00:25:06.070 --> 00:25:06.956
Are you going to talk?

00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:08.886
Who else was in on it?

00:25:10.200 --> 00:25:11.160
Who else?

00:25:12.270 --> 00:25:13.110
Fine.

00:25:13.350 --> 00:25:15.350
I'll tell Director Huang.

00:25:16.160 --> 00:25:17.240
You all just wait.

00:25:17.840 --> 00:25:18.680
Everybody, just wait.

00:25:18.680 --> 00:25:19.520
I did it.

00:25:31.550 --> 00:25:32.790
Do a flip for me.

00:25:32.790 --> 00:25:33.830
I don't buy it.

00:25:33.830 --> 00:25:35.750
I've trained for years longer. Watch.

00:25:36.720 --> 00:25:38.550
- Put it in.
- I'm way better.

00:25:38.550 --> 00:25:39.750
I've been training for 8 years.

00:25:39.750 --> 00:25:41.030
How long have you trained?

00:25:41.550 --> 00:25:44.070
Level the bricks. Make it steady.

00:25:44.680 --> 00:25:46.160
I'm better than all of you.

00:25:46.160 --> 00:25:47.696
Do a flip. Come on, that's easy.

00:25:47.707 --> 00:25:48.720
If you're so good, do one.

00:25:48.720 --> 00:25:50.510
I'm way better than you.

00:25:52.960 --> 00:25:54.160
Is this high enough?

00:25:55.310 --> 00:25:56.240
Yeah, yeah.

00:25:56.240 --> 00:25:57.550
- That's fine.
- Hold it steady.

00:25:57.550 --> 00:25:58.640
None of you can beat me.

00:25:58.640 --> 00:26:00.200
I'll flip now. Watch.

00:26:00.750 --> 00:26:01.590
Go over there.

00:26:01.790 --> 00:26:04.000
What was that? Get down.

00:26:05.400 --> 00:26:07.310
This sweater is gorgeous.

00:26:07.590 --> 00:26:08.430
Right?

00:26:08.936 --> 00:26:10.160
I was afraid it'd be too long.

00:26:10.160 --> 00:26:11.110
The size is just right.

00:26:11.110 --> 00:26:12.160
Exactly. Look.

00:26:12.160 --> 00:26:13.550
The style, the color.

00:26:13.830 --> 00:26:15.000
How can it look this good?

00:26:16.510 --> 00:26:18.070
You were born beautiful.

00:26:18.440 --> 00:26:20.000
You must've been stunning when young.

00:26:20.000 --> 00:26:20.880
How would you know?

00:26:21.160 --> 00:26:22.960
Director Huang has perfect taste.

00:26:24.070 --> 00:26:25.720
Now, that's what I like to hear.

00:26:25.720 --> 00:26:26.960
Come on, have some watermelon.

00:26:27.510 --> 00:26:28.510
Thank you, Yinwa.

00:26:29.920 --> 00:26:30.760
Yinwa,

00:26:30.960 --> 00:26:32.830
I brought yarn and needles.

00:26:32.830 --> 00:26:34.350
I'll teach you to knit a sweater.

00:26:34.350 --> 00:26:36.270
Then you can knit for Director Huang.

00:26:36.830 --> 00:26:38.550
Aren't you rehearsing Hong Deng Ji?

00:26:38.830 --> 00:26:40.030
You still have time to knit?

00:26:40.440 --> 00:26:42.440
I'm just a stand-in. It's fine.

00:26:42.960 --> 00:26:43.800
What's a stand-in?

00:26:44.110 --> 00:26:46.350
The kind who rehearses
and never performs.

00:26:47.510 --> 00:26:49.510
How can you be that vixen's stand-in?

00:26:50.550 --> 00:26:52.310
She has more stage experience than I do.

00:26:52.880 --> 00:26:55.000
Plus, she's well-connected.

00:26:55.270 --> 00:26:56.283
There's nothing I can do.

00:26:56.720 --> 00:26:58.000
How is she well-connected?

00:27:02.510 --> 00:27:03.350
What's wrong?

00:27:03.880 --> 00:27:06.350
I knitted my sister the exact same one.

00:27:06.350 --> 00:27:08.830
Seeing you is like seeing my sister.

00:27:10.510 --> 00:27:12.550
Then don't treat me
like the Director's wife.

00:27:12.561 --> 00:27:13.510
Treat me as your sister.

00:27:13.510 --> 00:27:14.920
Let's be sisters. What do you think?

00:27:16.070 --> 00:27:16.910
Really?

00:27:17.920 --> 00:27:19.510
I get to have such a kind sister?

00:27:20.270 --> 00:27:21.880
And I get such a pretty sister.

00:27:21.880 --> 00:27:23.070
I'm the lucky one.

00:27:24.830 --> 00:27:26.200
Then what do I call Director Huang?

00:27:26.550 --> 00:27:27.510
Call him Zhengjing.

00:27:28.000 --> 00:27:28.840
Is that appropriate?

00:27:29.240 --> 00:27:30.110
Why wouldn't it be?

00:27:30.880 --> 00:27:31.720
Yinwa,

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:35.270
Zhengjing is upset.

00:27:36.300 --> 00:27:41.220
(Main Cast: Li Yuhe-Li Gang,
Li Tiemei, Grandma Li)

00:27:41.240 --> 00:27:42.480
Our troupe

00:27:43.240 --> 00:27:44.720
is reviving Hong Deng Ji.

00:27:46.750 --> 00:27:48.350
As Director Huang requested,

00:27:49.830 --> 00:27:52.160
we'll hold
a democratic creative meeting.

00:27:52.830 --> 00:27:53.920
We need

00:27:54.440 --> 00:27:55.866
to discuss it together.

00:27:55.877 --> 00:27:56.960
(Main Cast of Hong Deng Ji)

00:27:56.960 --> 00:28:00.830
Who should play Li Tiemei

00:28:01.240 --> 00:28:02.920
and Grandma Li?

00:28:05.030 --> 00:28:06.680
Given where the troupe stands now,

00:28:07.070 --> 00:28:08.476
I don't need to spell it out, right?

00:28:08.830 --> 00:28:09.960
Everyone knows the situation.

00:28:10.350 --> 00:28:11.190
Director,

00:28:12.073 --> 00:28:13.266
why don't you say a few words?

00:28:15.790 --> 00:28:17.030
I haven't fully decided yet.

00:28:17.590 --> 00:28:18.880
Hu Sanyuan, you go first.

00:28:21.960 --> 00:28:22.880
I abstain.

00:28:22.880 --> 00:28:23.960
No abstaining.

00:28:25.030 --> 00:28:27.240
Everyone has to speak up today.

00:28:28.270 --> 00:28:29.790
Who picks a cast like this?

00:28:30.920 --> 00:28:32.550
This is meant to turn

00:28:32.550 --> 00:28:34.030
people against people.

00:28:35.880 --> 00:28:36.750
Hu Sanyuan,

00:28:37.350 --> 00:28:40.070
this is a democratic meeting,
not a struggle session.

00:28:40.070 --> 00:28:41.920
You're using democracy as a cover

00:28:42.510 --> 00:28:44.400
to stir conflict and split us up.

00:28:44.400 --> 00:28:45.830
Don't blow this out of proportion.

00:28:47.070 --> 00:28:49.030
The issues have always been there.

00:28:49.880 --> 00:28:51.113
I'm holding this meeting today

00:28:51.240 --> 00:28:53.030
to bring those issues into the open

00:28:53.030 --> 00:28:54.350
and then deal with them.

00:28:54.350 --> 00:28:55.640
No comment.

00:29:07.510 --> 00:29:08.920
If no one will, I'll go first.

00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:10.840
Go ahead.

00:29:18.160 --> 00:29:19.270
Last night,

00:29:20.240 --> 00:29:21.510
someone performed

00:29:21.510 --> 00:29:22.836
Grandma Li's spoken lines for me.

00:29:23.590 --> 00:29:24.720
Full of rise and fall.

00:29:25.160 --> 00:29:26.440
Bursting with passion.

00:29:26.440 --> 00:29:27.750
Deeply stirring.

00:29:28.880 --> 00:29:30.680
It got my blood pumping.

00:29:31.550 --> 00:29:33.310
I was moved to tears.

00:29:34.270 --> 00:29:35.550
Who delivered it that well?

00:29:35.550 --> 00:29:37.000
They should play Grandma Li.

00:29:38.550 --> 00:29:39.390
It was me.

00:29:41.510 --> 00:29:42.350
Cross-gender casting?

00:29:43.550 --> 00:29:44.680
I'll drum for you.

00:29:44.680 --> 00:29:46.720
I'll make it shine. Trust me.

00:29:48.310 --> 00:29:49.150
We're in a meeting.

00:29:53.350 --> 00:29:54.440
Mi Lan, go on.

00:29:55.160 --> 00:29:57.000
A performance that brilliant

00:29:57.510 --> 00:29:59.310
takes true mastery

00:29:59.310 --> 00:30:00.920
and years onstage.

00:30:01.400 --> 00:30:03.510
That's how it moves people.

00:30:04.110 --> 00:30:06.030
With my skills, age,

00:30:06.400 --> 00:30:08.550
voice, and presence,

00:30:09.200 --> 00:30:11.030
I can't carry Grandma Li's role.

00:30:11.350 --> 00:30:12.440
You're overthinking it.

00:30:13.160 --> 00:30:14.350
That was just a show for me.

00:30:15.920 --> 00:30:17.830
Deputy Director Zhu, Director Glasses.

00:30:18.550 --> 00:30:19.720
If you have any ideas,

00:30:19.720 --> 00:30:20.960
you can come straight to me.

00:30:21.510 --> 00:30:23.680
Am I really that scary?

00:30:24.750 --> 00:30:27.510
No need to send some fool in first.

00:30:27.510 --> 00:30:29.240
Who are you calling a fool?

00:30:29.590 --> 00:30:30.430
Director Huang.

00:30:31.350 --> 00:30:32.550
I'm an actress too.

00:30:32.550 --> 00:30:34.070
I can knit too.

00:30:34.310 --> 00:30:35.790
I can sing Grandma Li too.

00:30:36.160 --> 00:30:39.830
♪During the labor strike♪

00:30:41.160 --> 00:30:45.200
♪Your parents died so tragically♪

00:30:45.200 --> 00:30:46.510
Enough. Enough. Stop.

00:30:46.713 --> 00:30:47.932
Stop making a fool of yourself.

00:30:48.110 --> 00:30:49.310
I think it's worth discussing.

00:30:49.310 --> 00:30:51.000
She's got my vote too.

00:30:51.000 --> 00:30:52.200
What's there to discuss?

00:30:52.200 --> 00:30:53.040
Enough.

00:30:54.070 --> 00:30:54.910
Here's my decision.

00:30:55.400 --> 00:30:56.350
Hua Caixiang

00:30:56.830 --> 00:30:57.670
will play Li Tiemei.

00:30:58.160 --> 00:30:59.286
Mi Lan will play Grandma Li.

00:30:59.640 --> 00:31:00.480
Meeting dismissed.

00:31:01.790 --> 00:31:03.920
Director Huang, why can't I sing?

00:31:14.620 --> 00:31:16.420
(Li Tiemei: Hua Caixiang;
Grandma Li: Mi Lan)

00:31:16.440 --> 00:31:17.280
It's settled.

00:31:19.070 --> 00:31:19.910
Congratulations.

00:31:21.110 --> 00:31:21.950
What are you doing?

00:31:24.790 --> 00:31:26.400
Director Huang, don't be mad.

00:31:26.410 --> 00:31:27.310
I've talked

00:31:27.310 --> 00:31:28.510
with my wife.

00:31:28.510 --> 00:31:29.790
I'm keeping score for you.

00:31:33.110 --> 00:31:33.950
Go back first.

00:31:34.440 --> 00:31:35.280
Okay.

00:31:41.000 --> 00:31:42.720
Why the long face? What's wrong?

00:31:43.160 --> 00:31:44.720
Why make me play Grandma Li?

00:31:45.160 --> 00:31:46.510
How am I like Grandma Li?

00:31:47.750 --> 00:31:48.590
What do you think?

00:31:50.160 --> 00:31:52.240
You can't take on Hua Caixiang,

00:31:52.790 --> 00:31:54.510
so you pick on me instead.

00:31:55.200 --> 00:31:56.270
That's not fair.

00:32:03.400 --> 00:32:04.310
Mi Lan,

00:32:05.050 --> 00:32:05.910
after all these years,

00:32:05.940 --> 00:32:07.790
your work hasn't improved much,

00:32:09.960 --> 00:32:10.830
but your scheming

00:32:10.830 --> 00:32:13.000
has gotten pretty polished.

00:32:13.000 --> 00:32:14.680
I don't know what you mean.

00:32:15.400 --> 00:32:17.310
You learned to get inside my camp

00:32:17.680 --> 00:32:19.640
and work your way behind me.

00:32:21.590 --> 00:32:23.590
I was just caring for your wife.

00:32:23.590 --> 00:32:25.400
Isn't that supporting the team?

00:32:27.000 --> 00:32:28.073
Is that how you support us?

00:32:29.270 --> 00:32:30.750
By sending anonymous letters?

00:32:32.800 --> 00:32:33.960
The moment I got that letter,

00:32:33.960 --> 00:32:35.400
I knew exactly what was going on.

00:32:36.310 --> 00:32:37.150
And you guys still...

00:32:44.350 --> 00:32:45.190
Here's the thing.

00:32:45.750 --> 00:32:47.160
Tell me the truth today.

00:32:47.880 --> 00:32:48.790
Who taught you that?

00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:54.830
Zhu Jiru?

00:32:58.030 --> 00:32:58.920
Do you want to know?

00:33:01.160 --> 00:33:02.000
I'm not telling you.

00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:20.840
Mi Lan.

00:33:23.400 --> 00:33:24.830
I really must congratulate you.

00:33:25.400 --> 00:33:26.750
You're really something.

00:33:26.750 --> 00:33:28.310
Really something.

00:33:34.020 --> 00:33:42.500
(Li Tiemei: Mi Lan;
Grandma Li: Hua Caixiang)

00:33:58.160 --> 00:33:59.000
Sanyuan.

00:34:04.110 --> 00:34:05.070
Thank you.

00:34:06.680 --> 00:34:07.550
Why thank me?

00:34:07.550 --> 00:34:08.750
It had nothing to do with me.

00:34:09.110 --> 00:34:10.590
I know what really happened.

00:34:13.920 --> 00:34:17.030
Hua Caixiang said
she couldn't call you Grandma.

00:34:18.260 --> 00:34:19.120
Do you know

00:34:19.130 --> 00:34:21.350
your biggest difference?

00:34:22.790 --> 00:34:24.960
Hua Caixiang loves the show.

00:34:25.310 --> 00:34:26.960
You love being onstage.

00:34:28.310 --> 00:34:29.680
You've got to love the show.

00:34:33.400 --> 00:34:34.300
Aren't you rehearsing?

00:34:35.720 --> 00:34:36.560
I need the bathroom.

00:34:43.440 --> 00:34:44.400
♪Tiemei♪

00:34:44.400 --> 00:34:45.550
♪Stand tall♪

00:34:45.550 --> 00:34:48.400
♪Listen to me♪

00:34:52.720 --> 00:34:56.880
♪During the labor strike♪

00:34:58.790 --> 00:35:02.880
♪Your parents♪

00:35:12.830 --> 00:35:17.070
♪Died so tragically in cruel hands♪

00:35:17.070 --> 00:35:25.440
♪Li Yuhe toiled for the cause♪

00:35:25.440 --> 00:35:35.790
♪He vowed to keep
the martyrs' red lantern burning♪

00:35:35.790 --> 00:35:37.750
♪He wiped away the bloodstains♪

00:35:37.750 --> 00:35:39.830
♪Buried the bodies♪

00:35:39.830 --> 00:35:43.270
♪And returned to the fight♪

00:35:43.270 --> 00:35:45.710
♪Now♪

00:35:48.360 --> 00:35:51.190
You have to tough it out,
again and again.

00:35:55.000 --> 00:35:55.840
Keep going.

00:37:01.300 --> 00:37:05.740
(Art and literature serve
the poor and lower-middle peasants)

00:37:13.550 --> 00:37:15.150
We've made it to my hometown.

00:37:15.840 --> 00:37:16.800
How do you know?

00:37:17.110 --> 00:37:18.800
I took this road into town.

00:37:26.420 --> 00:37:29.620
(Taking opera to the countryside)

00:37:36.580 --> 00:37:40.020
(Art and literature serve
the poor and lower-middle peasants)

00:37:50.180 --> 00:37:52.660
(Performing opera for the people)

00:37:55.840 --> 00:37:56.960
Girls go first.

00:37:56.960 --> 00:37:58.000
Boys follow.

00:37:58.000 --> 00:37:59.400
Come on, line up. Quickly.

00:37:59.400 --> 00:38:00.510
Everyone, listen up.

00:38:00.510 --> 00:38:01.350
At ease.

00:38:02.400 --> 00:38:03.240
Attention.

00:38:03.590 --> 00:38:04.880
Left face.

00:38:05.190 --> 00:38:06.590
Forward march.

00:38:06.590 --> 00:38:10.400
♪We are all members
of the Communist Children's League.♪

00:38:10.400 --> 00:38:14.070
♪The future will surely be ours♪

00:38:14.070 --> 00:38:16.110
(Welcome, County Troupe)
♪Dee-dee-da, dee-da♪

00:38:16.110 --> 00:38:18.150
♪Dee-dee-da, dee-da♪

00:38:25.550 --> 00:38:27.110
♪Are you ready♪

00:38:27.110 --> 00:38:29.070
♪Always ready♪

00:38:29.070 --> 00:38:33.150
♪We are all members
of the Communist Children's League.♪

00:38:33.150 --> 00:38:36.840
♪The future will surely be ours♪

00:38:36.840 --> 00:38:40.670
♪Dee-dee-da, dee-da♪

00:38:40.670 --> 00:38:44.630
♪Little brothers and sisters♪

00:38:44.630 --> 00:38:48.710
♪Our future is limitless♪

00:38:48.710 --> 00:38:52.710
♪Hand in hand, always ready♪

00:38:52.710 --> 00:38:56.710
♪Dee-dee-da, dee-da♪

00:39:02.500 --> 00:39:03.360
Hold it steady.

00:39:03.360 --> 00:39:04.200
Steady.

00:39:07.070 --> 00:39:07.920
Sanyuan, Nail.

00:39:07.920 --> 00:39:09.510
Help pass me that light. Here.

00:39:09.510 --> 00:39:10.350
Okay.

00:39:10.710 --> 00:39:11.550
Can you manage?

00:39:11.670 --> 00:39:12.510
No problem.

00:39:15.190 --> 00:39:16.030
Here.

00:39:16.400 --> 00:39:18.030
Here we go. Move.

00:39:20.000 --> 00:39:20.840
Yi Qing'e.

00:39:21.190 --> 00:39:22.110
That hangs straight.

00:39:22.110 --> 00:39:23.360
Are you happy to be back home?

00:39:25.070 --> 00:39:26.590
We'll perform here for two days.

00:39:26.590 --> 00:39:28.510
I sent word to your parents.

00:39:28.800 --> 00:39:30.110
They'll watch the opera tomorrow.

00:39:30.400 --> 00:39:31.440
You'll get to see them.

00:39:32.150 --> 00:39:33.550
I want to go home and tend sheep.

00:39:33.960 --> 00:39:34.800
No time for that.

00:39:35.070 --> 00:39:35.910
You need to practice.

00:39:36.360 --> 00:39:37.440
Go on, go.

00:39:39.800 --> 00:39:40.640
Sanyuan.

00:39:42.440 --> 00:39:43.280
Sanyuan.

00:39:43.440 --> 00:39:44.280
Hu Sanyuan.

00:39:45.280 --> 00:39:46.120
Mr. Qin.

00:39:46.760 --> 00:39:47.630
I planned

00:39:47.630 --> 00:39:49.110
to visit after these shows.

00:39:49.110 --> 00:39:49.950
What brings you here?

00:39:50.510 --> 00:39:51.760
Let's go. Why are you frozen?

00:39:55.880 --> 00:39:58.320
♪Listen to me♪

00:39:58.820 --> 00:40:00.740
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

00:40:00.760 --> 00:40:03.400
♪During the labor strike♪

00:40:06.280 --> 00:40:09.230
♪Your parents♪

00:40:18.670 --> 00:40:22.360
♪Died so tragically in cruel hands♪

00:40:22.360 --> 00:40:29.440
♪Li Yuhe toiled for the cause♪

00:40:29.440 --> 00:40:38.030
♪He vowed to keep
the martyrs' red lantern burning♪

00:40:38.030 --> 00:40:40.960
♪He wiped away the bloodstains,
buried the bodies♪

00:40:40.960 --> 00:40:44.590
♪And returned to the fight♪

00:40:44.590 --> 00:40:46.510
♪Now♪

00:40:46.510 --> 00:40:48.440
Jerk!

00:40:56.110 --> 00:40:58.036
The commune made noodle soup.

00:40:58.047 --> 00:40:59.309
Everyone, go eat in the canteen.

00:40:59.320 --> 00:41:00.710
Okay.

00:41:08.710 --> 00:41:09.550
I'm done.

00:41:10.760 --> 00:41:12.230
Come on. Hurry up.

00:41:37.030 --> 00:41:37.870
What's up?

00:41:38.920 --> 00:41:40.320
Let's go somewhere.

00:41:43.150 --> 00:41:44.550
There are noodles in the canteen.

00:41:48.630 --> 00:41:50.070
Why does your uncle act like a spy?

00:41:50.280 --> 00:41:51.710
So secretive with Shoes Bai.

00:41:54.920 --> 00:41:55.760
Comrades,

00:41:56.150 --> 00:41:59.000
tonight's show was a great success.

00:42:01.680 --> 00:42:02.550
Quick, quick.

00:42:02.670 --> 00:42:03.880
Applause, applause!

00:42:04.710 --> 00:42:06.150
Especially Grandma Li.

00:42:06.440 --> 00:42:07.550
She sang the best.

00:42:08.070 --> 00:42:09.590
The orchestra backed her up well.

00:42:09.920 --> 00:42:11.150
Noodles are here!

00:42:11.960 --> 00:42:13.190
These noodles are great too.

00:42:14.170 --> 00:42:15.230
Have more if you like them.

00:42:15.403 --> 00:42:16.510
Here, I'll get you dry ones.

00:42:16.840 --> 00:42:17.680
Here.

00:42:17.960 --> 00:42:19.230
There is, there is.

00:42:19.960 --> 00:42:22.150
That lead drummer has real power.

00:42:23.150 --> 00:42:24.110
I heard

00:42:24.510 --> 00:42:27.190
that the drummer came from our commune.

00:42:27.840 --> 00:42:29.630
Yeah. His name is Hu Sanyuan.

00:42:30.920 --> 00:42:32.150
Hu Sanyuan.

00:42:47.710 --> 00:42:48.550
Here, over here.

00:42:52.320 --> 00:42:53.160
Who is it?

00:42:53.280 --> 00:42:54.550
It's me. Open the door.

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:06.940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

00:43:08.860 --> 00:43:10.210
Shoes Bai is missing.

00:43:10.210 --> 00:43:11.330
Gather some people

00:43:11.330 --> 00:43:12.400
and search along the river.

00:43:12.740 --> 00:43:13.920
Didn't your uncle leave with Shoes Bai?

00:43:13.920 --> 00:43:15.350
Don't talk nonsense, got it?

00:43:15.350 --> 00:43:16.780
It's been three years.

00:43:16.780 --> 00:43:18.580
They never got to be together.

00:43:20.760 --> 00:43:22.580
That man of Shoes Bai's,

00:43:22.910 --> 00:43:23.950
how did he end up here?

00:43:24.760 --> 00:43:25.740
Who is it?

00:43:27.860 --> 00:43:29.850
On day one of our rural performance tour,

00:43:29.850 --> 00:43:31.470
and it had to be you involved.

00:43:31.760 --> 00:43:33.360
Director, Hu Sanyuan admitted it.

00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:41.620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:43:43.090 --> 00:43:47.930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:43:49.370 --> 00:43:53.560
♪We met and brushed past♪

00:43:55.120 --> 00:44:02.420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

00:44:16.790 --> 00:44:20.540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

00:44:22.140 --> 00:44:27.710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

00:44:28.830 --> 00:44:32.890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

00:44:34.020 --> 00:44:39.610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

00:44:40.770 --> 00:44:44.970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

00:44:46.010 --> 00:44:51.640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

00:44:52.810 --> 00:44:57.500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

00:44:58.180 --> 00:45:03.350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

00:45:04.020 --> 00:45:09.050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:15.510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:45:15.890 --> 00:45:21.170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

00:45:22.120 --> 00:45:27.930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

00:45:27.930 --> 00:45:33.350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

00:45:33.900 --> 00:45:39.410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

00:45:39.960 --> 00:45:44.920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

00:45:45.940 --> 00:45:51.220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

00:45:52.020 --> 00:46:01.050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪